sible and timely data collection. Regional follow-up and review will be based on national-level analyses and contribute to follow-up and review at the global level.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"padding-3-percent\" column_padding_position=\"top-bottom\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/2\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1518544332203{padding-right: 10% !important;}\"]The UK is a signatory member state; on behalf of the UK Government, the work will be led in Northern Ireland by DAERA, the Department of Agriculture, Environment and Rural Affairs, which will have reporting responsibilities.</p>\n<p>The Sustainable Development Goals are a common blueprint for a sustainable future; they are relevant to developed nations as well as developing countries; they are applicable to communities, to households and individuals, as well as to governments, businesses and the voluntary sector.</p>\n<p>You can find out much more about the Sustainable Development Goals <a href=\"https://sustainabledevelopment.un.org/sdgs\">here</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type=\"in_container\" full_screen_row_position=\"middle\" scene_position=\"center\" text_color=\"dark\" text_align=\"left\" top_padding=\"0%\" bottom_padding=\"8%\" overlay_strength=\"0.3\" shape_divider_position=\"bottom\" shape_type=\"\"][vc_column column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/1\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" phone_text_alignment=\"default\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][image_with_animation image_url=\"5902\" alignment=\"center\" animation=\"Fade In\" border_radius=\"none\" box_shadow