ng to shape the sustainability agenda in Northern Ireland, promoting and demonstrating the benefits of adopting the principles of sustainable development. He has worked with many public sector organisations to help them understand the scope of their legislative responsibilities and to embed the structural arrangements needed to comply with their obligations.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"padding-3-percent\" column_padding_position=\"top-bottom\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/2\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1518553472481{padding-right: 10% !important;}\"]He can help clients to meet their economic, environmental and social responsibilities by providing expert advice on the design and implementation of effective sustainability strategies[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type=\"in_container\" full_screen_row_position=\"middle\" scene_position=\"center\" text_color=\"dark\" text_align=\"left\" overlay_strength=\"0.3\" shape_divider_position=\"bottom\"][vc_column column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/1\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" phone_text_alignment=\"default\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][vc_column_text]We offer a range of services:\r\n\r\n<strong>Independent research on sustainability:</strong> we can provide the evidence to support decision-making towards the achievement of good sustainability practice within an organisations. We work on issues such as the implications of climate change, land use, sustainable food systems, environmental quality, approaching each topic by combining sound science with policy analysis.\r\n\r\n<strong>Strategic planning for sustainability: </strong>we can offer advice and guidance on the design and content of strategies for sustainable development. Drawing on years of experience in the creation of regional strategies for Northern Ireland as well as individual plans for councils and other public sector organisations, we can tailor our advice to organisational requirements.\r\n\r\n<strong>Sustainability Reporting: </strong>we can help organisations to assess how and to what extent sustainability has been integrated into their culture, policies and practices. By working alongside colleagues within an organisation, we can combine our specialist expertise with their corporate knowledge to undertake a practical and pragmatic assessment and advise on future developments.\r\n\r\n<strong>Sustainable Food: </strong>On behalf of the city of Belfast, we wrote a successful bid to be included as one of only six founder members of the UK Sustainable Food Cities programme and, subsequently, to win the first of the SFC awards. With more than 40 towns and cities now in that network, we can share our experience to help other districts establish initiatives to tackle some of the social, environmental and economic impacts of food that will help to improve the health and wellbeing of their residents.\r\n\r\n<strong>Chairing and Facilitating: </strong>Drawing on long experience of leading and participating in group sessions at every scale, from small deliberative seminars to full-scale conferences, we can provide the appropriate level of input to meet your needs.\r\n\r\n<strong>Keynote Speaker: </strong>Jim Kitchen has spoken at conferences and other events, frequently and widely, on many aspects of sustainability, from transport to wildlife trade, from climate to conservation, from food to fisheries. He can tailor his presentations for a wide range of audiences.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type=\"full_width_background\" full_screen_row_position=\"middle\" bg_color=