INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("5995", "1", "2018-02-18 15:02:55", "2018-02-18 15:02:55", "[vc_row type=\"full_width_background\" full_screen_row_position=\"middle\" bg_color=\"#ffffff\" scene_position=\"center\" text_color=\"dark\" text_align=\"left\" top_padding=\"8%\" bottom_padding=\"8%\" overlay_strength=\"1\" shape_divider_position=\"bottom\" shape_type=\"\"][vc_column column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/1\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" phone_text_alignment=\"default\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][vc_row_inner column_margin=\"default\" text_align=\"left\"][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/2\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][nectar_gradient_text heading_tag=\"h2\" color=\"extra-color-gradient-1\" gradient_direction=\"diagonal\" text=\"About\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/2\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner column_margin=\"default\" text_align=\"left\"][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"padding-3-percent\" column_padding_position=\"top-bottom\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/1\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][vc_column_text]Jim Kitchen is an independent researcher. His work embraces environmental and sustainability policymaking and strategic planning, for clients in the public sector, the business community and for voluntary and community organisations. He is a Board member of Northern Ireland Environment Link and sits on the Steering Group of Climate Northern Ireland. He is also a member of the RSAs Food, Farming and Countryside Commission. In October 2010, he was appointed as a Visiting Professor in the Faculty of Art, Design and the Built Environment at Ulster University.\r\n\r\nHe has been an advisor to the British Council in Northern Ireland on climate change, is a former Board member of Arena Network, the environmental arm of Business in the Community and was a Council member of the Ulster Wildlife Trust.\r\n\r\nIn 2017, Jim retired as Director of Sustainable Northern Ireland, a charity working with partners to promote the adoption of sustainable development principles by public authorities and others. He also founded and managed the Belfast Food Network, a project to establish Northern Irelands first Sustainable Food City.\r\n\r\nEarlier, from 2007-11, Jim was the Northern Ireland Director of the Sustainable Development Commission, working with government Ministers, advisers and officials to embed sustainability in government policy. Prior to that, he established and developed the NI office of WWF, the worlds leading environmental organisation.\r\n\r\nHe has championed the promotion of sustainability in the built environment in Northern Ireland. He advised the Royal Society of Ulster Architects in the production of its first sustainable design guide, judged sustainable buildings competitions for the Construction Employers Federation and the Royal Town Planning Institute, as well as the annual environmental awards of BITC and Action Renewables. His work in this field was recognised by the award of an honorary Fellowship of the Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors.\r\n\r\nOther significant work has included:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #2ecc71;\">NI Sustainable Development Implementation Strategy</span>: led the negotiation process to compile the strategy; brokered the integration of sustainability into governmental processes and policy; drafted the governments guidance on compliance with the SD Statutory Duty.</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #2ecc71;\">NI Green New Deal</span>: Participated in a cross-sectoral body of business and non-governmental organisations developing a strategy for a low-carbon economy in Northern Ireland.</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #2ecc71;\">NI Climate Change</span>: represented NI in the UK Governments Climate Change Risk Assessment process.</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #2ecc71;\">Public Events</span>: Published, broadcast and spoken at conferences, frequently and widely, on sustainability themes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nJims early career was as a teacher and Headmaster, thirteen years of which were spent in Zambia, where he pursued and developed his passion for the natural world and its wildlife.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type=\"full_width_background\" full_screen_row_position=\"middle\" bg_color=\"#333333\" scene_position=\"center\" text_color=\"light\" text_align=\"left\" top_padding=\"8%\" bottom_padding=\"8%\" color_overlay=\"#2ecc71\" overlay_strength=\"1\" shape_divider_position=\"top\" shape_divider_height=\"250\" shape_type=\"tilt_alt\"][vc_column centered_text=\"true\" column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/6\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" phone_text_alignment=\"default\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][/vc_column][vc_column centered_text=\"true\" column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"2/3\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" 