nner column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/2\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][nectar_gradient_text heading_tag=\"h2\" color=\"extra-color-gradient-1\" gradient_direction=\"horizontal\" text=\"Introduction\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/2\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner column_margin=\"default\" text_align=\"left\"][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"padding-3-percent\" column_padding_position=\"top-bottom\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/2\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1518539373055{padding-right: 10% !important;}\"]In September 2015, 193 member states of the United Nations ratified the UNs Sustainable Development Goals. In that treaty, the international community made the following commitment:\r\n\r\nWe resolve, between now and 2030, to end poverty and hunger everywhere; to combat inequalities within and among countries; to build peaceful, just and inclusive societies; to protect human rights and promote gender equality and the empowerment of women and girls; and to ensure the lasting protection of the planet and its natural resources\r\n\r\nWhile the SDGs are not legally binding, governments are expected to take ownership and establish national frameworks for the achievement of the 17 Goals. Countries have the primary responsibility for follow-up and review of the progress made in implementing the Goals, which will require quality, accessible and timely data collection. Regional follow-up and review will be based on national-level analyses and contribute to follow-up and review at the global level.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding=\"padding-3-percent\" column_padding_position=\"top-bottom\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/2\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1518544332203{padding-right: 10% !important;}\"]The UK is a signatory member state; on behalf of the UK Government, the work will be led in Northern Ireland by DAERA, the Department of Agriculture, Environment and Rural Affairs, which will have reporting responsibilities.\r\n\r\nThe Sustainable Development Goals are a common blueprint for a sustainable future; they are relevant to developed nations as well as developing countries; they are applicable to communities, to households and individuals, as well as to governments, businesses and the voluntary sector.\r\n\r\nYou can find out much more about the Sustainable Development Goals <a href=\"https://sustainabledevelopment.un.org/sdgs\">here</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row type=\"in_container\" full_screen_row_position=\"middle\" scene_position=\"center\" text_color=\"dark\" text_align=\"left\" top_padding=\"0%\" bottom_padding=\"8%\" overlay_strength=\"0.3\" shape_divider_position=\"bottom\" shape_type=\"\"][vc_column column_padding=\"no-extra-padding\" column_padding_position=\"all\" background_color_opacity=\"1\" background_hover_color_opacity=\"1\" column_shadow=\"none\" column_border_radius=\"none\" width=\"1/1\" tablet_text_alignment=\"default\" phone_text_alignment=\"default\" column_border_width=\"none\" column_border_style=\"solid\"][image_with_animation image_url=\"5902\" alignment=\"center\" animation=\"Fade In\" border_radius=\"none\" box_shadow=\"none\